The paper deals with partial orders on probability distributions and density operators, which are concepts commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The discussion of domain theory and possible applications in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and natural language processing (cs.AI) also suggest these categories. Finally, the use of order theory (cs.DS) in Chapter 1 further supports the likelihood of these categories.
